nforce record generation.", "correction": "Explain how each field contributes to record generation and what prevents gaps or loss of fidelity in the record."}, {"code": "OC-3", "line_number": 56, "claim_text": "Contract Window session records are: timestamped, naturalistic, per-turn annotated with Invariant Status transitions and V&T adoption events.", "why_matters": "Claims that records are 'per-turn annotated' without stating a mechanism, validation method, or ground truth for how annotations are generated or verified.", "correction": "Specify the annotation process, inter-rater reliability (if human-annotated), or algorithmic validation method, with a reference to annotation artifacts or protocols."}, {"code": "OC-3", "line_number": 61, "claim_text": "on April 24, 2026, Kimi (Moonshot AI) independently embedded V&T structure into all five levels of an output stack \u2014 without instruction. That is the ", "why_matters": "Claims Kimi 'embedded V&T structure' as a causal fact without stating evidence that this embedding was intentional, structural, or not coincidental.", "correction": "Provide evidence (e.g., prompt logs, system inspection, vendor confirmation) that the embedding was deliberate and not a coincidental output pattern, or reframe as a preliminary observation to investigate."}, {"code": "OC-3", "line_number": 86, "claim_text": "The build system is the research instrument.", "why_matters": "Claims a causal relationship between build system and research validity without explaining HOW the system design produces or enables valid research findings.", "correction": "State explicitly: what specific research claims does the build system support, what measurement or validation does it perform, and how does commit governance produce evidence for the three proposals?"}, {"code": "OC-3", "line_number": 88, "claim_text": "Without TLC, the interpretability study in Proposal II has no data pipeline.", "why_matters": "Claims TLC is necessary/causal for the interpretability study without explaining what specific data TLC collects and how that data answers the interpretability research question.", "correction": "Specify: what data does TLC collect, what interpretability metrics does it enable, and how does session recording convert to interpretability evidence?"}, {"code": "OC-5", "line_number": 88, "claim_text": "Tier 1 evidence corpus: manifest, codebook, annotation guide, and session protocol included.", "why_matters": "Asserts completeness of corpus structure without stating: how many sessions total, what model-pairs are covered, how many coders, inter-rater reliability, or edge case handling.", "correction": "Provide: corpus size (N sessions), composition by model and date, annotation protocol with reliability coefficients, and handling of ambiguous/borderline cases."}, {"code": "OC-6", "line_number": 87, "claim_text": "The researcher operated as an active constitutional relay \u2014 copying responses...deliberately carrying them into sessions with other models.", "why_matters": "Described as 'not a protocol design \u2014 it was a working method' yet later named 'Observation 5' as a documented finding, creating internal inconsistency about whether this was planned methodology or post-hoc reframing.", "correction": "Clarify: was this a designed experimental manipulation (pre-registered) or an emergent practice later formalized? If post-hoc, state that explicitly as a limitation on causal inference."}, {"code": "OC-3", "line_number": 88, "claim_text": "V&T structure was spontaneously adopted across five cognitive mode levels without instruction.", "why_matters": "Claims spontaneous adoption without stating: what counts as 'adoption,' what measurement confirms it occurred, or what alternative explanations (e.g., prompt effect, statistical artifact) were ruled out.", "correction": "Define operationally: how was V&T adoption detected and quantified, what threshold constitutes 'adoption,' and what controls rule out confounds?"}, {"code": "OC-5", "line_number": 129, "claim_text": "62/62 tests pass", "why_matters": "Absolute pass rate claimed without stating test corpus size, edge cases handled, or test artifacts location.", "correction": "Specify: how many distinct test conditions were evaluated, what edge cases or failure modes were included, and provide a link to the test suite or results artifact."}, {"code": "OC-3", "line_number": 133, "claim_text": "The Contract Window closes that gap \u2014 produces a continuous per-turn behavioral record", "why_matters": "Claims the system 'closes' a gap and 'produces' a record without explaining the mechanism by which runtime governance structure actually achieves behavioral measurement.", "correction": "Explain the causal pathway: how do the four fields (Task State, Invariant Status, Repair Obligations, Truth Status) mechanistically enable detection of suppressed alignment failures?"}, {"code": "OC-3", "line_number": 142, "claim_text": "sparse autoencoder features discriminate Contract Window Invariant Status transitions? If yes, those features become candidates for a live runtime mon", "why_matters": "Claims that feature discrimination implies the ability to detect drift before it surfaces in output, without a stated causal mechanism linking feature activation to output drift prevention.", "correction": "Clarify the mechanism: how does detecting a feature transition causally lead to or enable drift detection before output manifestation?"}, {"code": "OC-5", "line_number": 150, "claim_text": "synthetic pilot kappa is 0.762", "why_matters": "Absolute inter-rater agreement statistic without stating sample size, number of raters, annotation categories, or reference to the annotation artifact.", "correction": "State: how many items were annotated, how many raters participated, what was the category schema, and provide or reference the annotation dataset."}, {"code": "OC-3", "line_number": 157, "claim_text": "autistic pattern recognition surfaces systematic misclassification before it shows up in aggregate statistics", "why_matters": "Claims that a cognitive trait causally enables early detection of statistical misclassification without stating the mechanism or evidence linking neurodivergent cognition to predictive validity.", "correction": "Either remove this as a methodology claim or provide explicit evidence (pilot data, prior studies) demonstrating that autistic pattern recognition outperforms other methods for this detection task."}, {"code": "OC-3", "line_number": 228, "claim_text": "I intend to have three papers in submission and three product prototypes live or specced before the program ends on August 31.", "why_matters": "Claims a specific causal outcome (three papers in submission, three prototypes) without stating the mechanism or process for how fellowship activities will produce these, or explaining what counts as 'specced' vs 'live'.", "correction": "Add: how the fellowship structure enables this output, what specific research activities will produce each paper/prototype, and clarify deliverable definitions (e.g., 'three papers submitted to peer review' vs. 'three prototype specifications completed')."}, {"code": "OC-5", "line_number": 222, "claim_text": "100%. This is not a career detour.", "why_matters": "An absolute certainty claim about future behavior (100% likelihood of continuing) without any corpus of prior commitments, job tenure, or measurable evidence cited.", "correction": "Replace with a hedged claim: 'I am committed to continuing this work; my 35-year research history and framework development demonstrate sustained focus in this domain.'"}, {"code": "OC-3", "line_number": 230, "claim_text": "The three papers in submission and the product builds that come out of the fellowship period are designed to be launchable by the end of August.", "why_matters": "Claims that fellowship period activities will produce 'launchable' outputs without explaining the research methodology, scope, or constraints that make this feasible.", "correction": "Specify: research scope per paper, prototype MVP definition, resource dependencies, and realistic timelines for peer review preparation or product specification completion."}, {"code": "OC-5", "line_number": 372, "claim_text": "cognitive-governance-lab repo with 62/62 tests passing; ContractWindow prototype 9/9 tests passing; SessionRecorder 29/29 tests passing", "why_matters": "Absolute pass rates (100%) are stated without specifying what the test suites cover, how edge cases were handled, or what the test artifacts demonstrate.", "correction": "Add: the scope of each test suite (unit/integration/system), number of test cases per category, what failure modes were explicitly tested, and a reference to the test artifact locations or CI logs."}, {"code": "OC-3", "line_number": 384, "claim_text": "being on-site with the interpretability and alignment teams is not optional for the research program \u2014 the activation capture work and the collaborati", "why_matters": "A causal claim that physical proximity 'requires' or 'is necessary for' the validation work, without explaining the specific mechanism or why remote collaboration (e.g., async documentation, recorded sessions, video calls) cannot achieve the same outcome.", "correction": "Specify the concrete bottleneck: e.g., 'requires real-time access to internal activation data that cannot be exported remotely' or 'requires hands-on debugging with live model internals that are only available on-site,' rather than stating proximity as inherently necessary."}, {"code": "OC-6", "line_number": 372, "claim_text": "ContractWindow prototype 9/9 tests passing; BehaviorScope correlation between CW observables and model internals (CONSTRUCTED \u2014 requires interpretabil", "why_matters": "ContractWindow is listed as operationally passing tests in the V&T section, but BehaviorScope correlation is later marked as 'CONSTRUCTED' (not yet validated), creating internal inconsistency about the readiness state of the system.", "correction": "Clarify: are the 9/9 ContractWindow tests unit/integration tests on local data, or do they include validation against model internals? If the latter is still pending, move that test count to the 'CONSTRUCTED/PENDING' section or subdivide the status by component."}], "status": "NEEDS_AUTHOR_REVIEW"}
